{"word":"ἀποκτείνω","slug":"ἀποκτείνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀποκτείνω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <a href='S:ἀποκτίννυμι'><el>ἀποκτίννυμι</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> rare, <a href='S:ἀποθνήσκω'><el>ἀποθνήσκω</el></a> being used as <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to kill, slay</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of judges, <i>to condemn to death</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, like <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>enecare, to weary to death</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}